The paper proposes a method for explaining the predictions of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves decomposing the pre-activation prediction of a neural network into a linear combination of activations of training points, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the importance of training points on the learned parameters of the network, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.CL, in that order.
